article.headline: Toledo 61, Miami (Ohio) 56
article.story: TOLEDO, Ohio (AP) -- Keonta Howell and Kashif Payne scored 15 points apiece Saturday night, and Toledo remained unbeaten in the Mid-American Conference with a 61-56 victory over Miami of Ohio. Toledo (11-8, 7-0) matched a school record by winning its first seven MAC games. The 1978-79 team also opened 7-0 in conference play. Howell had a jumper and a layup during an 8-0 run that put Toledo ahead to stay early in the second half. Miami (8-11, 4-3) trailed by as many as 10 points down the stretch. Toledo overcame a poor shooting night by guard Justin Ingram, who went 2-of-15 from the field and 0-for-7 on 3-point shots. Ingram came in averaging 15.8 point per game. Tim Pollitz scored 25 points for Miami on 11-of-14 shooting. Nathan Peavy scored 13 points, had 12 rebounds and blocked four shots. The game matched the conference's two stingiest defenses, both holding opponents to 61 points per game. Toledo had 10 steals, three of them during the pivotal 8-0 run that made it 38-31 early in the second half. Toledo leads the conference with an average of 9.2 steals per game.
